        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 16 at 4:53PM MDT by NWS Great Falls MT</headline>
        <description>At 453 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms 7 miles southeast of Lothair, or 10 miles southwest of
Chester, moving northeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Chester, Joplin, The Knees, Inverness, Lothair, Gildford, Hingham,
Rudyard, and Tiber Dam.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
